{"title":"Wilde Updates the Supertramp","link":"https://theradavist.com/wilde-updates-the-supertramp/","date":1744989862000,"content":"<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde_Supertramp_Touring_Bike-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde_Supertramp_Touring_Bike-01.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde_Supertramp_Touring_Bike-01.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde_Supertramp_Touring_Bike-01.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><em><a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/wilde-bikes/\" target=\"_blank\">Wilde Bicycle Co</a>‘s <a href=\"https://alnk.to/fwsM7hv\" target=\"_blank\">Supertramp</a> is its all-rounder, do-everything rigid mountain bike. With a steel fork, boost-spaced chassis, and large front triangle for optimized frame bag space, it’s as capable as a bicycle camping sled as it is a singletrack jibber and everything in-between. The Minneapolis-based brand just announced a few key updates for the new 2025 batch…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-4.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-4.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-21.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-21.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Supertramp Updates Quick Hits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Frameset is <strong>$1300 </strong></li>\n<li>Complete is <strong>$2900</strong></li>\n<li>UDH Compatible</li>\n<li>Smaller head tube diameter (EC 34/34 headset) for a bit more compliant ride</li>\n<li>New Colorway: Dirt Champagne</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-3.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-3.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde_Supertramp_Geometry_2025.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde_Supertramp_Geometry_2025.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde_Supertramp_Geometry_2025.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde_Supertramp_Geometry_2025.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Geometry</h3>\n<p>For 2025, the geometry remains the same as previous models. It’s designed to have a stable, off-road touring geometry with a tall stack height, a longish reach to maximize front triangle space and allow the use of a modern short stem, and a trail number that balances off-road handling characteristics with the ability to carry a front load confidently.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-17.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-17.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>2025 Supertramp Frame Specs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Clearance for 29 x 2.6″ tires</li>\n<li>Headset: EC 34/34 Dirt Champagne</li>\n<li>73mm English threaded bottom bracket shell</li>\n<li>Post Mount</li>\n<li>Boost Spacing</li>\n<li>Seatpost: 31.6mm</li>\n<li>Seat Collar: 35.0</li>\n<li>Cable Guides: Modular guides under the downtube, and full loop braze-ons on the stays (No Zip Ties)</li>\n<li>12mm Thru Axle – 1.5 x 178mm</li>\n<li>Dirt Champagne Frames are UDH Compatible</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-15.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-15.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-15.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-15.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-2.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-2.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Supertramp Fork Specs</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Clearance for 29 x 2.8″ tires</li>\n<li>ISO disc mounts</li>\n<li>110mm Boost Spacing</li>\n<li>15mm Thru Axle – 1.5 x 135mm</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-24.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-24.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-24.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.us-east-1.amazonaws.com/uploads/2025/04/Wilde-Supertramp-2025-Updates-24.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://alnk.to/fwsM7hv\" target=\"_blank\">Wilde Bikes</a>.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/wilde-updates-the-supertramp/\">Wilde Updates the Supertramp</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"67c16af19e94de51ae5d3e7b07ed4e759e280e61d92ab93250b7e247316eaad2","category":"Cycling"}